body: Hi M Amrutha Our parents constantly worry about us, and sometimes the pressure can become overbearing. Some concerns are justifiable while some others can be downright unreasonable. Our expert IDP counsellors are here to help you map a plan to manage their expectations. Here are a few areas to get you started: 1. Education Loan So, to help you manage funds for your international education, we have partnered with ICICI Bank to offer Smart Education Loans <https://go-prod.idp.com/MTY2LUhNVC03MjEAAAGZ0wu4v8cNPkz9gR6_XIxv9VToyb8c3NmZc8VWvj27nETYDS8Q21Zw-bLyBlOy7waOYQeMybc=> to students like you. 2. Accomodation If you are worried about where you will stay in Australia, don‚Äôt be! As always, IDP has got you covered. As part of our Student Essential Services, we help you find your find an accommodation <https://go-prod.idp.com/MTY2LUhNVC03MjEAAAGZ0wu4v6ouVOzTkBaW4zrY8IUwveoP1lmAyW7R_PUGvfqA25vtlQ11fcsGT0AtoYKqzGu9Tyc=> in Australia that best fits your needs.. 3. Bank Account Now is the time for you to open and pre-fund a bank account to manage your finances efficiently in the new country. To make the process easier for you, IDP has partnered with some of the most credible banks as part of our Student Essential Services <https://go-prod.idp.com/MTY2LUhNVC03MjEAAAGZ0wu4vz6qnERjRHwR5ToWyevxD56-wdJb1jPcdjVkJ25DH03D3fOWNXZ0RpsI_GJ9zg-tjPI=> 4. Heatlh Insurance It‚Äôs only a matter of time before you start living your education dream. Let‚Äôs use this waiting period to get you a comprehensive personal health insurance plan <https://go-prod.idp.com/MTY2LUhNVC03MjEAAAGZ0wu4vwYRZFmcCz0ks4v3C-doBfrb6jR32GzaUChjMsc2EomcOvVzrLpSulVchBgSPlWGPsM=>. As part of our Student Essential Services, we can connect you with credible healthcare services 5. Money Transfer It is now time to chalk out a plan to send money for your tuition and living expenses to the Institution. It is important to do this carefully. This is why we have partnered with Cohort Go, Flywire, and Western Union as part of IDP‚Äôs Student Essential Services. <https://go-prod.idp.com/MTY2LUhNVC03MjEAAAGZ0wu4v6O3p3IBYjpup713XKUUQcBoEfDCfZ_M_q9_iFALPhOD3iWSY4FGjY1yJmb2snB9RwA=> 6. Sim Card IDP have partnered with telecommunication partners for specific destinations that allow you to access reliable and flexible pre or post-paid sim plans <https://go-prod.idp.com/MTY2LUhNVC03MjEAAAGZ0wu4vyTrwtd76Q_BNqoUSjCEqnIiStDMh2bFIlE0sLcPqDxFF5PfoAXpNU8voyhrmFcy4Gs=> that offer you the freedom to choose how you use your mobile device. body: Dear M Amrutha Sridhanya, You've come a long way already. You've taken the IELTS Pre-test and faced your English fears head-on. That's fantastic! subject: AIMO 2025 Progress Prize 2 Competition Wrap-Up!
snippet: Hi Amrutha Sridhanya, The AI Mathematical Olympiad (AIMO) 2025 Progress Prize 2 competition has officially concluded! This year's challenge asked participants to develop algorithms and models
body: Kaggle Hi Amrutha Sridhanya, The AI Mathematical Olympiad (AIMO) 2025 Progress Prize 2 competition has officially concluded! This year's challenge asked participants to develop algorithms and models capable of solving complex math problems. The competition brought together a diverse and talented community, all working to advance AI's capabilities in mathematical reasoning. We're excited to share that participants tackled an even more challenging dataset this year and delivered outstanding results. The top performing solution achieved an impressive 68% accuracy rate, a significant improvement over last year, highlighting the rapid progress being made in the field of AI-driven mathematical problem-solving. To dive into the winning approaches and explore key takeaways from the competition, check out the leaderboard and winner solution write-ups below: View the Leaderboard Happy Kaggling! body: Emailer The Spring Harvest! April is an interesting time in the Indian agricultural calendar. In the north and the west, it marks the end of the Rabi season, while farmers in the east get ready to harvest their Boro rice. While much of the south has gathered the dry-season crops, they too celebrate the coming of spring and prepare for a new beginning. In this issue, let us journey through India and discover its springtime traditions. # 1 Crops, Culture & Celebrations Punjab erupts in bhangra for Baisakhi. Assam greets Bohag Bihu with a soulful call of the pepa, a traditional hornpipe. In Kerala, people begin the new year with the first sight of Vishukkani, a vibrant display of spring‚Äôs bounty. Here‚Äôs how every corner of India celebrates the season of renewal. # 2 A Feast Across Regions From the fields to your table, explore recipes featuring the freshest yield of the spring harvest. Recreate the delicious flavours of the season in your kitchen, including the saffron-hued Meethe Chawal of Punjab, the tangy, spicy Mango Thokku of Tamil Nadu, and more. # 3 Be it Bihu or Baisakhi, the new harvest calls for a celebration! Share your recipe for a festival-special dish for a chance to win a bb gift card worth Rs. 500 Contest ends on: 15 April 2025 # 4 Harvest Festival Recipe Inspirations Powered By Spread the word! Online grocery shopping has never been easier. Need things fresh? Whether it‚Äôs fruits and vegetables or dairy and meat, we have this covered as well! subject: Competition Launch: Yale/UNC-CH - Geophysical Waveform Inversion
snippet: Hi Amrutha Sridhanya, Tuning a radio through static to catch a signal is a lot like analyzing seismic data. You know something important is there, but pinpointing it is the challenge. Geophysicists
body: Kaggle Hi Amrutha Sridhanya, Tuning a radio through static to catch a signal is a lot like analyzing seismic data. You know something important is there, but pinpointing it is the challenge. Geophysicists face this daily, searching for what lies beneath the Earth's surface. In this competition, you'll build ML models to improve Full Waveform Inversion (FWI), a technique used to map underground structures by analyzing seismic waves. The goal is to combine physics and ML to increase the speed, accuracy, and reliability of FWI‚Äîeven with noisy and incomplete data. Total Prizes: $50,000 Entry Deadline: June 23, 2025 Learn More Your work could improve subsurface imaging for renewable energy exploration, medical diagnostics, or material analysis applications. Good luck, Walter Reade Kaggle Data Scientist Kaggle, Inc 1600 Amphitheatre Pkwy Mountain View, CA 94043 This email was sent to sridhanya1045@gmail.com because you indicated that you'd like to receive news and updates about Kaggle. Discover the keys to unlocking your future with the comprehensive insights offered by Clickastro's Astrology Combo Report. This unique report combines the power of astrology, gemstone recommendations, and numerology to provide you with a detailed roadmap for success and fulfillment in life. At the core of the Astrology Combo Report lies the In-depth analysis of your life based on Vedic astrology. By examining the positions of the planets at the time of your birth, this report offers accurate predictions and personalized insights into various aspects of your life, including career, relationships, health, and more. Gain a deeper understanding of yourself and your potential as you explore the intricate details of your horoscope. body: Application Number: N826390244 Programme: IRIS@NUS Dear Miss Amrutha Sridhanya Madduri, We hope this email finds you well. We would like to inform you of the outcome of your recent application for the IRIS @ NUS programme at the National University of Singapore. We regret to inform you that your application was unsuccessful. The decision is final and no appeals will be allowed. We sincerely appreciate your interest in our programme and the time and effort you put into your application. Our selection process was highly competitive, with over 7,000 applications received, which made the decision-making process incredibly challenging. Please remember that the outcome of this application does not diminish your accomplishments or qualifications. It is important to recognize that there are many factors involved in the selection process, and the decision does not reflect your potential or abilities. We would like to encourage you to keep pursuing your academic and professional goals. We believe you have a bright future ahead, and we are confident that you will find success in your chosen field. If you are entering your final year of study this year, you are very welcome to apply to our PhD and Master's programme at NUS <https://nusgs.nus.edu.sg/programmes/>. Thank you once again for considering us and for the time you invested in your application. We wish you all the best in your future endeavors. Best Regards, NUS Graduate School National University of Singapore This is a system-generated message. Any replies to this message will not be received. subject: Competition Launch: Image Matching 2025
snippet: Hi Amrutha Sridhanya, Finishing a puzzle can be hard enough, but what if pieces from other puzzles were mixed in, too? This makes the task even harder since you now have to find only the pieces you
body: Kaggle Hi Amrutha Sridhanya, Finishing a puzzle can be hard enough, but what if pieces from other puzzles were mixed in, too? This makes the task even harder since you now have to find only the pieces you need. The same challenge applies to building 3D scenes from real-world image sets, where unrelated photos are lumped together with relevant ones, complicating accurate scene reconstruction. In this competition, you'll train a machine learning model to sort through mixed image collections, group the right ones, and rebuild accurate 3D scenes. Total Prizes: $50,000 Entry Deadline: June 2, 2025 Learn More Your work could improve how we use images in augmented reality, robotics, and even scientific research. Good luck, Sohier Dane Kaggle Data Scientist Kaggle, Inc 1600 Amphitheatre Pkwy Mountain View, CA 94043 This email was sent to sridhanya1045@gmail.com because you indicated that you'd like to receive news and updates about Kaggle. FII flows were robust during the week as they net bought Rs 27,392 cr in the cash market while DIIs net sold Rs 849 cr till 27th March. Trump announced a 25% tariff on imports of automobiles and select auto components from April 02 which triggered fresh concerns over the growth of the US economy. Mar‚Äô25 Manufacturing/Services PMI for both US and India, monthly auto sales numbers and quarterly provisional business updates from banks will be the key things to track next week. Enter the name of your new folder, decide who can access it (make the folder personal or shared), and click Create. To create a subfolder, click ‚Äú...‚Äù next to a parent folder and select Create subfolder. Move documents to specific folders by clicking ‚Äú...‚Äù next to a file and selecting More > Move to Folder. Or simply drag and drop a file in the desired folder. subject: Competition Launch: ARC Prize 2025

body: Kaggle Hi Amrutha Sridhanya, We are in an idea constrained world in the race toward true Artificial General Intelligence (AGI). This means conceptual progress can come from anyone. While models today excel at processing data they struggle with adapting to new challenges. The ARC Prize 2025 competition dares innovators to think beyond conventional AI, designing systems that learn and reason like humans, unlocking the next frontier of artificial intelligence. In this competition, you'll build AI systems that can efficiently learn new skills and tackle open-ended problems, without relying solely on large language models (LLMs) trained on massive datasets. We're challenging you to beat the Abstraction and Reasoning Corpus (ARC-AGI-2) benchmark. The top submissions will demonstrate progress toward human-like reasoning benchmarks. Total Prizes: $725,000 Entry Deadline: October 27, 2025 Learn More Your work could contribute to new AI problem-solving applicable across industries. Good luck, Walter Reade Kaggle Data Scientist Kaggle, Inc 1600 Amphitheatre Pkwy Mountain View, CA 94043 This email was sent to sridhanya1045@gmail.com because you indicated that you'd like to receive news and updates about Kaggle. body: Hey there, and welcome on board! üéâ You're all set to start designing, testing, and collaborating on APIs. Here‚Äôs how to hit the ground running. Verify API behavior Send requests <https://learning.postman.com/docs/sending-requests/requests/> and inspect responses to ensure that your API works as expected. Send Sample Request <https://postman.postman.co/redirect/workspace?type=team&entity=request> Create a source of truth Bring all your collections <https://learning.postman.com/docs/getting-started/first-steps/creating-the-first-collection/> , environments, and resources together for easy access. Set Up Your Workspace <https://go.postman.co/redirect/workspace?type=personal&recentlyVisited=true> Work together on your APIs Share requests, debug issues, and collaborate with your teammates in real-time. Invite Your Team <https://go.postman.co/settings/team/members> Postman is better on the app Test local APIs seamlessly, verify API performance, and do a lot more with the powerful desktop app. Download Desktop App <https://www.postman.com/downloads/> Helpful resources for getting started Learning Hub Learn how to set up and use Postman. body: Debt Free Companies Harness the power of SSL Research! Dear AMRUTHA SRIDHANYA MADDURI, At SBI Securities, we believe in empowering you with insights to make informed investment decisions. In this email, we'll delve into the attractive characteristics of debt-free companies. What are Debt-Free Companies? Debt-free companies are those that operate businesses without any outstanding debt obligations. These companies have effectively managed their finances to eliminate dependence on borrowed funds, showcasing financial stability and resilience. What Invest in Debt-Free Companies? Financial Stability: Without the burden of debt, these companies are less vulnerable to economic downturns and interest rate fluctuations. Higher Profitability: Reduced interest expenses can lead to higher profit margins and increased shareholder returns (Return on Equity). Greater Flexibility: Debt-free companies have greater flexibility to invest in growth opportunities, research and development, and innovation. Stronger Resilience: These companies are better equipped to withstand market volatility and economic uncertainties. Easy Funding for future: These companies generally have better credit rating profile thus helping it to borrow any future fund requirement at a competitive rate. Key Parameters Related to Debt: Debt-to-Equity Ratio (Total Debt/Equity or Net Worth): Measures the proportion of debt to equity used to finance a company's assets. A lower ratio indicates lower debt dependences. Interest Coverage Ratio (EBIT/Interest): Indicates a company's ability to cover its interest expenses with its earnings. A higher ratio suggests stronger financial health and greater ability to service its debt. Return on Equity (ROE): Measures a company's profitability in relation to its shareholders' equity. Higher ROE generally indicates efficient use of shareholders‚Äô money. subject: Competition Launch: FGVC12 2025
snippet: Hi Amrutha Sridhanya, Put your computer vision skills to the test with this series of research competitions that focus on fine-grained categorization - differentiating between plant or animal species,
body: Kaggle Hi Amrutha Sridhanya, Put your computer vision skills to the test with this series of research competitions that focus on fine-grained categorization - differentiating between plant or animal species, for example - that pushes the limits of both human and machine performance. You can find these competitions on our new community spotlight shelf on our main page. Help advance image categorization research when you classify marine animals into taxonomic categories, identify plants using quadrat images, or re-identify animals based on unique traits, among others. We are excited to host the competitions supporting the Fine-Grained Visual Categorization (FGVC12) workshop at the 2025 Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition Conference (CVPR 2025) in Nashville, the foremost computer vision event of the year. AnimalCLEF25 @ CVPR-FGVC & LifeCLEF FungiCLEF25 @ CVPR-FGVC & LifeCLEF PlantCLEF2025 @ LifeCLEF & CVPR-FGVC GeoLifeCLEF25 @ CVPR & LifeCLEF FathomNet 2025 @ CVPR-FGVC Participate in one or all of the FGVC Competitions to expand the field of computer vision. Good luck, Maggie Demkin Kaggle Competitions Kaggle, Inc 1600 Amphitheatre Pkwy Mountain View, CA 94043 This email was sent to sridhanya1045@gmail.com because you indicated that you'd like to receive news and updates about Kaggle. If you don't want to receive these emails in the future, please unsubscribe here. You can also change your preferences on your account's profile page by logging in at kaggle.com.

body: MAILER Dear Soundarya, Unlock a detailed understanding of your personality, strengths, and challenges through the holy trinity of Vedic Astrology ‚Äî the In-depth Horoscope, Gem Recommendation Report, and Numerology Report. Together they serve as your ultimate guide for making informed life decisions, exploring relationship dynamics, and fostering spiritual growth. The In-Depth Horoscope gives you in-depth insights into your life by understanding the alignment of planets at the time of your birth. This report offers valuable perspectives on your career, relationships, and key moments in life. With this report, you can learn to enhance favourable planetary influences and mitigate bad fortunes, promoting your overall physical and emotional balance. The Gem Recommendation report lets you achieve prosperity and growth by leveraging the power of gemstones. It identifies the gems that resonate with your unique astrological profile, helping to neutralize negative influences and amplify positive energies. Wearing the recommended gems enhances your vitality and well-being, aligning your energy with that of the planets. The Numerology Report reveals the significance of the numbers related to your birthdate and name. This report provides insights into your personality traits, life path, and potential challenges, fostering self-awareness. Understanding your numerological profile helps you predict life cycles, offering a framework for personal growth and informed decision-making. Together, these three reports offer you a comprehensive approach to rid yourself of doshas permanently. By integrating these insights, you align your life with the cosmic order, paving the way for a balanced, prosperous, and harmonious existence. subject: Competition Launch: BirdCLEF+ 2025
snippet: Hi Amrutha Sridhanya, Mobile and habitat-diverse species play a vital role in tracking biodiversity changes, but traditional observation methods are challenging. With passive acoustic monitoring (PAM)
body: Kaggle Hi Amrutha Sridhanya, Mobile and habitat-diverse species play a vital role in tracking biodiversity changes, but traditional observation methods are challenging. With passive acoustic monitoring (PAM) and machine learning, we can now analyze audio data to better understand the impact of ecological restoration efforts. This year's BirdCLEF+ competition expands from BirdCLEF 2024 by incorporating not only bird species but also amphibians, mammals, and insects from Colombia's Middle Magdalena Valley, a critical biodiversity hotspot. You'll develop ML models that identify these species by their acoustic signatures, with a focus on the limited training data available for endangered species. Total Prizes: $50,000 Entry Deadline: May 29, 2025 Learn More Your work could help researchers track species more effectively and better understand the impact of ecological restoration. Good luck, Sohier Dane Kaggle Data Scientist Kaggle, Inc 1600 Amphitheatre Pkwy Mountain View, CA 94043 This email was sent to sridhanya1045@gmail.com because you indicated that you'd like to receive news and updates about Kaggle. If you don't want to receive these emails in the future, please unsubscribe here. You can also change your preferences on your account's profile page by logging in at kaggle.com.

body: MACRO TRENDS ‚Äì MONTHLY ECONOMIC DATA Harness the power of SSL Research! <http://lnk.sbisecurities.info/vtrack?clientid=123363&ul= VVMEXQEHV0QIGUYWDwVcAAwaWFBWAVd5AQkDWglNAg4OTk8=&ml=UloIUwcCUglFVUlXU1QMUB4=&sl=IR5yGH98Hmt0MUkICAoaEgAKSgQFQBBQEg0HQEsKDwcMTgM=&pp=0&fl=CxZFFEUITRdOEkJKFQNdEgcATBMPQQtcFUoLXUoFCA0GQVYRQlJKS0ADQgFYRVULSkFWR10QFRYXKVMGQlYQVFM2QwFYVhFndApbEA4NTURQU3wCCVsNVA8HRwFVMQQRDEBHPHJSWkMAUx80fXE=&ext=> Dear AMRUTHA SRIDHANYA MADDURI, We are pleased to share with you the latest monthly macroeconomic data report that will provide insights into the current economic landscape. Key Highlights for the Month: Consumer Inflation stabilises with month on month decline in food prices India Manufacturing PMI hits 5-month high of 57.7 in Jan‚Äô25 UPI transaction volume at all-time high Fastag total transaction volume and value grow 14.8% and 19.0% YoY respectively in Jan‚Äô25 Gross GST Collection stood at its second-highest level of Rs 2.0 trillion in Jan‚Äô25, up 13.6% YoY and 10.5% MoM. Peak Power demand in Jan‚Äô25 grows to its 7-month high of 237 GW, up 6.6% YoY Domestic tractor sales grew 11.4% YoY in Jan‚Äô25, which is seasonally a weaker month New Demat account addition at 21-month low; Added 16.5 lakhs accounts in Jan‚Äô25 vs average of 31.9 lakhs during last 2 years Average Daily Turnover in the cash segment stood at its 14-month low of Rs 1,019 bn in Jan‚Äô25, down 8.0% MoM and 17.2% YoY FIIs outflow continues in the month of Feb‚Äô25; Have sold equities worth Rs 2.8 trillion during Oct‚Äô24 to Feb‚Äô25 Source: SSL Research Regards, Team SBI Securities body: MAILER Dear Soundarya, Unlock a detailed understanding of your personality, strengths, and challenges through the holy trinity of Vedic Astrology ‚Äî the In-depth Horoscope, Gem Recommendation Report, and Numerology Report. Together they serve as your ultimate guide for making informed life decisions, exploring relationship dynamics, and fostering spiritual growth. The In-Depth Horoscope gives you in-depth insights into your life by understanding the alignment of planets at the time of your birth. This report offers valuable perspectives on your career, relationships, and key moments in life. With this report, you can learn to enhance favourable planetary influences and mitigate bad fortunes, promoting your overall physical and emotional balance. The Gem Recommendation report lets you achieve prosperity and growth by leveraging the power of gemstones. It identifies the gems that resonate with your unique astrological profile, helping to neutralize negative influences and amplify positive energies. Wearing the recommended gems enhances your vitality and well-being, aligning your energy with that of the planets. The Numerology Report reveals the significance of the numbers related to your birthdate and name. This report provides insights into your personality traits, life path, and potential challenges, fostering self-awareness. Understanding your numerological profile helps you predict life cycles, offering a framework for personal growth and informed decision-making. Together, these three reports offer you a comprehensive approach to rid yourself of doshas permanently. By integrating these insights, you align your life with the cosmic order, paving the way for a balanced, prosperous, and harmonious existence. FIIs net sold Rs 6,423 cr while DIIs net bought Rs 3,776 cr in cash market during the week (DII data till 12th March). US Feb‚Äô25 CPI data came softer than expected increasing 2.8% YoY and 0.2% MoM. India CPI data eased to a 7-month low of 3.6% in Feb‚Äô25 vs. expectation of 4.0% largely driven by lower food prices. FOMC interest rate decision, weekly US jobless claims and India wholesale price inflation for Feb‚Äô25 will be key data points to track next week. We continue to remain cautiously optimistic on market due to the recent recovery as well as valuation easing. subject: [Model Launch] Gemma 3 Is Now on Kaggle!
snippet: Hi Amrutha Sridhanya, We're excited to introduce Gemma 3, a collection of lightweight open models built on the same advanced technology as Gemini 2.0. Designed for portability and speed, Gemma 3
body: Kaggle Hi Amrutha Sridhanya, We're excited to introduce Gemma 3, a collection of lightweight open models built on the same advanced technology as Gemini 2.0. Designed for portability and speed, Gemma 3 can run directly on devices, from smartphones to powerful workstations, empowering developers to create responsible AI applications at scale. With a range of sizes (1B, 4B, 12B, 27B), you can choose the best model for your needs. Access Gemma 3 Key Features: Global support: 140 languages, enabling truly localized AI experiences. Advanced reasoning: Process images, text, and video with superior AI capabilities. Large context window: 128K-token capacity for complex tasks. Powerful AI agents: Build intelligent agents with function calling and structured output. Explore the expanding Gemmaverse today and see how Gemma 3 can push your AI projects forward. Brenda Flynn Kaggle Partnerships Lead Kaggle, Inc 1600 Amphitheatre Pkwy Mountain View, CA 94043 This email was sent to sridhanya1045@gmail.com because you indicated that you'd like to receive news and updates about Kaggle. FIIs net sold equities worth Rs 25,247 cr while DIIs net bought Rs 18,631 cr (DII data till 06th March) in the cash market during the week. Drop in dollar index to 104 level, US 10-yr treasury yield to 4.2% and crude oil prices to below $70 per barrel are positive signs for the Indian equity market. Next week will be a truncated one owing to holiday on Friday due to Holi. We expect global cues along with inflation data from US and India to be closely tracked and will drive the overall investor sentiments. We remain cautiously optimistic on market due to recent recovery and valuation easing. subject: Competition Launch: BYU - Locating Bacterial Flagellar Motors 2025
snippet: Hi Amrutha Sridhanya, Macromolecular machines drive life at the microscopic scale, yet identifying them remains a challenge. The flagellar motor, essential for bacterial motility, is one such structure
body: Kaggle Hi Amrutha Sridhanya, Macromolecular machines drive life at the microscopic scale, yet identifying them remains a challenge. The flagellar motor, essential for bacterial motility, is one such structure - difficult to spot in 3D reconstructions due to noise, variable orientations, and crowded cellular environments. In this competition, you'll build ML models to scan 3D tomograms and spot flagellar motors in bacterial cells. Dive into the challenge and craft a model that decodes complex 3D tomograms and illuminates the hidden engines behind bacterial movement. Total Prizes: $65,000 Entry Deadline: May 28, 2025 Learn More Your work could improve cryogenic electron tomography (cryo-ET) analysis, helping researchers study infectious diseases, develop new medicines, and advance synthetic biology. Good luck, Walter Reade Kaggle Data Scientist Kaggle, Inc 1600 Amphitheatre Pkwy Mountain View, CA 94043 This email was sent to sridhanya1045@gmail.com because you indicated that you'd like to receive news and updates about Kaggle. If you don't want to receive these emails in the future, please unsubscribe here. You can also change your preferences on your account's profile page by logging in at kaggle.com.

subject: NUS Graduate Admission System 3 ‚Äì Reminder: Submit Your Application Before the Deadline
snippet: National University of Singapore Dear Amrutha Sridhanya, We hope this email finds you well. We wanted to remind you that the deadline to submit your application for the Internship and Research
body: Dear Amrutha Sridhanya, We hope this email finds you well. We wanted to remind you that the deadline to submit your application for the Internship and Research Immersion in Singapore (IRIS) @ NUS programme is fast approaching. We highly encourage you to complete and submit your application as soon as possible to ensure full consideration for admission. At NUS, we understand that applying to a university can be an exciting but also demanding process. To ensure that you have a smooth and successful application experience, we have compiled a few essential reminders: 1. Application Requirements: Please double-check that you have completed all the necessary sections of the application form. Ensure that you have filled in all required personal information, academic history, and supporting documents. 2. Supporting Documents: Make sure that you have submitted all the required supporting documents, such as transcripts, letters of recommendation, statement of purpose, or any other supplementary materials. Refer to the application guidelines or the program's website for specific document requirements. 3. Deadline: The deadline to submit your application is 5 March 2025. Please note that applications received after this deadline may not be considered. Do finalise and submit your application as soon as possible to avoid any last-minute technical difficulties or delays. Remember, this is your opportunity to showcase your unique qualities, experiences, and aspirations that make you a strong candidate for our university. We appreciate your interest in NUS and we look forward to reviewing your application. We wish you the best of luck in your application process! Regards, Graduate Admission System Administrator NUS Graduate School National University of Singapore This is a system-generated message. Any replies to this message will not be received. Please contact the programme administrator for further assistance. National University of Singapore 21 Lower Kent Ridge Road Singapore 119077 +65 6516 6666

subject: [Model Launch] Aya Vision Is Now on Kaggle!
snippet: Hi Amrutha Sridhanya, Welcome Aya Vision to Kaggle! Aya Vision is Cohere For AI's latest multilingual, multimodal model, designed to bridge language and vision. Excelling across 23 languages and
body: Kaggle Hi Amrutha Sridhanya, Welcome Aya Vision to Kaggle! Aya Vision is Cohere For AI's latest multilingual, multimodal model, designed to bridge language and vision. Excelling across 23 languages and multiple modalities, this state-of-the-art model supports tasks such as image captioning, visual question answering, text generation, and translating text and images into coherent output. Available in both 8B and 32B open-weight versions, it empowers researchers worldwide. Access Aya Vision Cohere for AI is also introducing the Aya Vision Benchmark, a rigorous multilingual and multimodal evaluation spanning 23 languages. Cohere's commitment to multilingual research spans collaborations with over 3,000 researchers from 119 countries, contributing to the Aya collection, Aya-101, and critical evaluation sets. We can't wait to see what you create with Aya Vision! Brenda Flynn Kaggle Partnerships Lead Kaggle, Inc 1600 Amphitheatre Pkwy Mountain View, CA 94043 This email was sent to sridhanya1045@gmail.com because you indicated that you'd like to receive news and updates about Kaggle. If you don't want to receive these emails in the future, please unsubscribe here. You can also change your preferences on your account's profile page by logging in at kaggle.com.

subject: Competition Launch: Stanford RNA 3D Folding
snippet: Hi Amrutha Sridhanya, If you sat down to complete a puzzle without knowing what it should look like, you'd have to rely on patterns and logic to piece it together. Predicting RNA's 3D structure
body: Kaggle Hi Amrutha Sridhanya, If you sat down to complete a puzzle without knowing what it should look like, you'd have to rely on patterns and logic to piece it together. Predicting RNA's 3D structure works the same way‚Äîusing only its sequence to figure out how it folds into the structures that define its function. In this competition, you'll develop machine learning models to predict an RNA molecule's 3D structure from its sequence. With limited data available, the challenge is to fine-tune models that can accurately capture RNA's complex folding patterns. Total Prizes: $75,000 Entry Deadline: May 22, 2025 Learn More Your work could help push RNA-based medicine forward, improving treatments for cancer and genetic diseases, and help biologists understand the origin and future of life.
